episodes.title: Revival
episodes.plot: Maul takes Savage as his apprentice and together they set out to gather an army. Their attempt to recruit Hondo Ohnaka and his pirates is interrupted by Jedi Council members Obi-Wan Kenobi and Adi Gallia.

episodes.title: A War on Two Fronts
episodes.plot: By a request from Lux Bonteri, Anakin, Obi-Wan, Ahsoka and Rex travel to Onderon to help train a group of rebels so they can take back the capital city of Iziz from the Separatists.

episodes.title: Front Runners
episodes.plot: The Jedi and Rex return to Coruscant and leave Ahsoka in charge of supervising the Onderon Rebels as they carry out a series of strikes in the capital.

episodes.title: The Soft War
episodes.plot: The Onderon Rebels attempt to rescue former King Dendup before he is executed.

episodes.title: Tipping Points
episodes.plot: The people of Onderon have decided to revolt against the Separatists, leading to a full scale revolt between the rebels and battle droids.

episodes.title: The Gathering
episodes.plot: Ahsoka escorts a group of younglings to Ilum where they meet with Yoda and seek out the Kyber crystals needed to build their own lightsabers.

episodes.title: A Test of Strength
episodes.plot: As the six younglings prepare to construct their lightsabers, their training vessel Crucible is attacked by Hondo Ohnaka and his pirates.

episodes.title: Bound for Rescue
episodes.plot: Hondo has failed to capture the Kaiburr crystals, but does hold Ahsoka as a prisoner. The younglings form a plan to infiltrate the pirate hideout on Florrum.

episodes.title: A Necessary Bond
episodes.plot: General Grievous leads an attack on Hondo Ohnaka's base, forcing the pirates to form a temporary alliance with Ahsoka and the Jedi younglings.

episodes.title: Secret Weapons
episodes.plot: R2-D2 joins a team of Republic Droids known as D-Squad, led by Colonel Gascon. Their mission: to steal an encryption module from a Separatist dreadnought.

episodes.title: A Sunny Day in the Void
episodes.plot: D-Squad has obtained their mission objective, but crash-land on a desolate planet after a run-in with comets.

episodes.title: Missing in Action
episodes.plot: Colonel Gascon and the five droids of D-Squad have arrived at the remote town of Pons Ora on the planet Abafar and find a clone commando suffering from amnesia.

episodes.title: Point of No Return
episodes.plot: Finally on their way back to Republic space, D-Squad uncovers a Separatist plan involving a sabotaged Jedi cruiser.

episodes.title: Eminence
episodes.plot: Darth Maul and Savage Opress join forces with the Death Watch and together they recruit the Black Sun and Hutt crime lords to form the Shadow Collective.

episodes.title: Shades of Reason
episodes.plot: The Sith brothers and their criminal allies attack Mandalore and the Death Watch pretends to defeat them, causing the gullible people to choose Pre Vizsla's rule over Duchess Satine's.

episodes.title: The Lawless
episodes.plot: Darth Maul has taken over leadership of Death Watch. Though the Jedi cannot officially interfere, Obi-Wan Kenobi travels to Mandalore to rescue Satine.

episodes.title: Sabotage
episodes.plot: Anakin and Ahsoka are tasked to investigate a bombing at the Jedi Temple since they were two of the few Jedi off-planet at the time it occurred.

episodes.title: The Jedi Who Knew Too Much
episodes.plot: When the suspect of the Temple bombing is murdered in her cell, Ahsoka suddenly finds herself framed and on the run from the Republic military.

episodes.title: To Catch a Jedi
episodes.plot: Ahsoka is on the run and hiding in the criminal underworld of Coruscant. She strikes up an unlikely alliance with a former enemy turned bounty hunter.

episodes.title: The Wrong Jedi
episodes.plot: Ahsoka is put on trial by the Jedi Council and must face the Galactic Senate. Anakin searches for a way to prove his Padawan's innocence.
